The Basics

Include the makeidx package with a \usepackage command.
Put a \makeindex command in the document preamble.
Put a \printindex command where the index it to appear---usually at the end, before the \end{document} command.
Run LaTeX on your .tex file to generate a .idx file.
Run makeindex on main.idx.
Rerun LaTeX on your .tex file to create a document with an index.
Do It Yourself

The easiest way to run through the process is to download this file, main.tex and run the following commands:
latex main.tex
makeindex main.idx
latex main.tex

